1
00:00:07,007 --> 00:00:11,967
Red Sorghum

2
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:21,977
Adaptation of Moyan's novels:
<<Red Sorghum>> and <<Kaoliang Spirit>>.

3
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:31,987
I want to tell you the story
about my grandparents.

4
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:38,994
People from my town still talk about them.

5
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:43,999
but not everyone believes the story anymore.

6
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:59,025
This is my grandma.

7
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:04,019
That year, on the 9th day of the 7th moon, my grandma was married off.

8
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:09,024
To Big Head Li, a wine brewery owner at 18 Mile Slope.

9
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:14,040
Big Head Li didn't find a wife till he was fifty.

10
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:19,034
Because everyone knew
that he was a leper.

11
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:28,043
No crying or vomiting in the sedan chair, it's bad luck!

12
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:35,050
Don't take off your veil either, it brings trouble!

13
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:41,056
Get in!

14
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:59,085
According to local custom...

15
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:04,079
The sedan bearers must tease the bride.

16
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:11,086
All the chair bearers and musicians are Big Head Li's employees.

17
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:16,091
There was only one man hired for the wedding.

18
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:19,105
He was a well known sedan bearer from the area.

19
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:24,099
He later became my grandpa.

20
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:11,157
Don't peek, little lady.

21
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:14,160
If you're bored, talk with us!

22
00:03:14,194 --> 00:03:17,163
It's a long trip.

23
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:22,157
Talk if you're bored, sing if you're tired.

24
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:23,169
Come on, sing!

25
00:03:23,203 --> 00:03:28,163
There is no use in peeking!

26
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:32,178
Little lady...it's not easy to carry you.

27
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:37,172
Yes, not easy.

28
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:42,177
Poor girl, what a pity.

29
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:46,181
Who'd marry their own flesh to a leper for money!

30
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,193
She will have a painful future.

31
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:50,196
Your parents sold you for money!

32
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:53,199
Big Head Li oozes yellow pus all over.

33
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,201
He will never recover.

34
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:58,204
Yes, he will never recover.

35
00:03:58,238 --> 00:04:03,198
You can not live with Big Head Lee.

36
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,211
Or you will rot, too.

37
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:07,213
Yes, you will rot, too.

38
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:10,216
It's not too late.

39
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:14,209
We can carry you back.

40
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:17,223
Just give us the word.

41
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:22,217
Come on, at least sing for us, while we sweat for you.

42
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:32,267
Not a word, huh? Let's shake her up!
Can't make her sing, at least, it'll make her piss.

43
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:38,233
Music!

44
00:04:57,233 --> 00:05:03,433
The guests aren't gone.
The party isn't over.

45
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:09,433
But can't find the groom

46
00:05:18,533 --> 00:05:24,633
Eager is the groom.

47
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:31,833
Rushes into the room to unveil
his bride.

48
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:44,033
Ah-ya-ya, my little darling.

49
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:58,433
A nose as flat as a pancake.

50
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:05,333
Gosh, big spots all over her face.

51
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:19,433
Chicken-skin neck, ugly face.

52
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:27,333
Hair covered with fleas.

53
00:06:28,133 --> 00:06:41,133
Ah-ya-ya, my little darling.

54
00:06:43,133 --> 00:06:47,333
Still silent? Let's continue.

55
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:54,533
Save me from the ugly bride.

56
00:06:55,333 --> 00:07:01,333
Turn around and run.

57
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:14,533
She's now crashing into my thigh.

58
00:07:16,633 --> 00:07:23,533
I'd rather sleep in the pig pen.

59
00:07:23,633 --> 00:07:33,633
Ah-ya-ya, my little darling.

60
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:51,426
Go!

61
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:16,451
On the way to 18 Mile Slope, you pass Green Killer's Crossing.

62
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:23,458
The area is covered with wild sorghum.

63
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:29,464
No one knew where it came from.  No one harvested it.

64
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:33,468
They all say that
these are wild sorghum.

65
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:38,473
And that the place is haunted.

66
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,515
Stop!

67
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:13,508
Don't move!

68
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:18,513
Put down the sedan.

69
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:29,524
Money!

70
